    <item>
      <title>Advanced Data Mining with Artificial Intelligence (BAT51201)</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/teaching/advanced-data-mining-with-artificial-intelligence-bat51201-unist/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 27 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/teaching/advanced-data-mining-with-artificial-intelligence-bat51201-unist/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This course is an introductory graduate-level course on data mining and artificial intelligence, specialized for the students majoring in management.
In this course, students will learn the most basic and core deep learning techniques and examine how deep learning techniques can improve business
problem-solving and decision-making. Moreover, the students will study practical examples to place data analysis in business context. In specific, this
course covers the concepts and applications of data preprocessing, regression analysis, clustering, neural networks, CNN, and RNN. To achieve these
objectives, this course uses a combination of lectures, in-class exercises, case studies, class discussions, assignment, exam (&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/Dawoon-Jeong0523/Lecture_UNIST_2024_Fall&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Lecture Code Link&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
